tissue_type: brain tumor cell line monolayer (atypical teratoid/rhabdoid tumor)
tissue_characteristics: tissue: brain tumor cell line monolayer (atypical teratoid/rhabdoid tumor)
growth_protocol_ch1: Tumor samples were snap frozen in liquid nitrogen or transferred to RNAlater immediately after surgical removal as part of patient care. All samples were collected with appropriate IRB approval (COM-IRB#95-500 and 09-0906 )
extraction_method: RNeasy (Qiagen) extraction of total RNA was performed according to the manufacturer's instructions.
labeling_method: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, 2001, Affymetrix).
hybridization_protocol: Following fragmentation, 11.5 ug of cRNA were hybridized for 16 hr at 45C on GeneChips. GeneChips were washed and stained in the Affymetrix Fluidics Station 450
scanner_type: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix Gene Chip Scanner 7G.
sample_description: analysis of atypical teratoid rhabdoid cell line
data_processing: Microarray .CEL file data was background corrected and normalized using the gcRMA algorithm, resulting in log 2 expression values.

labeling_method: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, 2001, Affymetrix).
hybridization_protocol: Following fragmentation, 11.5 ug of cRNA were hybridized for 16 hr at 45C on GeneChips. GeneChips were washed and stained in the Affymetrix Fluidics Station 450
scanner_type: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix Gene Chip Scanner 7G.
data_processing: Microarray .CEL file data was background corrected and normalized using the gcRMA algorithm, resulting in log 2 expression values.

scanner_type: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix Gene Chip Scanner 7G.
data_processing: Microarray .CEL file data was background corrected and normalized using the gcRMA algorithm, resulting in log 2 expression values.
